defaultThe readiness of local NHS and social care services to treat patients with long-term conditions (including multiple conditions) within the communitydefault3.1
defaultIn its June 2011 summary report the NHS Future Forum called for the commissioning of integrated care for patients with long
default-
defaultterm conditions, complex needs and at the end of life. It was an important acknowledgement that the ageing population and increased prevalence of chronic diseases requires a 
defaultdecisive 
defaultshift
default away
default from the current concentration of resources
default in acute 
defaulthospital 
defaultsettings
default towards greater preventive care, 
defaultself-care
default, more consistent standards of primary care and 
defaultcommunity based health and social care 
defaultservices that
default are 
defaultalso 
defaultwell coordinated.
default 
defaultThe Department of Health 
defaultsubsequently 
defaultapproached The King’s Fund and the Nuffield Trust for help in supporting the development of its national strategy on int
defaultegrated care. In our resulting 
defaultreport
default we identified a set of 
defaultorganisational and policy
default barriers that need to be addressed.
default 
default 
default 
default3.2
default defaultThey included: 
default3.3
default defaultSome
default local areas have attempted to 
defaultovercome
default these and other obstacles
default. 
defaultFor example the North West London Integrated Care Pilot (ICP) is a large scale innovative programme designed to improve the coordination of care for people over 75 years of age and adults living with diabetes.
default 
defaultM
defaultultidisciplinary groups of local care providers segment
default pa
defaulttients according to risk; share
default care plans
default across care settings; identify patients needing intensive case management, and mo
defaultnitor care plan implementation.
default 
defaultSophisticated governance structures have been put in place, with all
default staff involved in the pilot, together with representatives of local patie
defaultnt organisations and providers coming
default together 
defaultunder 
defaultan Integrated Management Board (IMB).
default Financial incentives have also been designed to support the aims of the pilot in relation to care planning, collaborative care management, and the development of innovative alternatives to hospital admission.
default3.4
default defaultLikewise NHS organisations in Trafford, a borough 
defaultof
default 215,000 people in Greater Manchester have been trying to develop closer collaboration between community based primary, general acute medicine, specialist outpatient and diagnostic care to enable more care to be delivered outside hospital. 
defaultInitial implementation of the programme involved nine ‘vanguard’ general practices working with community, acute and
default  
default 
defaultsocial care to redesign selected care pathways, share data, identify patients at risk of unplanned hospitalisation, and generally to act as a test bed for implementing and evaluating integrated care.
default3.5
default defaultNeither area is unique in attempting new ways to deliver care closer to the patient. However in terms of scope and ambition they are certainly not the norm. It is perhaps instructive that in both cases there were substantial initial prompts; in the case of Trafford, it was a 
defaultan ambitious PCT and groups of clinicians
default that 
defaultfunded and 
defaultdrove the need for change, while in North West London the set up phase was helped by financial and other support from NHS London; enabling investment in IT, pilot leadership, coordination of multidisciplinary groups and project management. 
defaultWhile recent Government announcements pledging to align policy initiatives in favour of more integrated care
default for a set of ‘pioneers’
default are welcome, it is
default 
defaultalso
default likely that
default other
default l
defaultocal examples of innovation w
defaultill
default emerge as a result of the current spending squeeze
default and 
defaultit is important that these are
default also
default supported and evaluated.
